
Overview of noun revolution

The noun revolution has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (6) revolution -- (a drastic and far-reaching change in ways of thinking and behaving; "the industrial revolution was also a cultural revolution")
2. (6) revolution -- (the overthrow of a government by those who are governed)
3. rotation, revolution, gyration -- (a single complete turn (axial or orbital); "the plane made three rotations before it crashed"; "the revolution of the earth about the sun takes one year")
